President Obama spoke with UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon about the international response to the Ebola epidemic in West Africa. They discussed the need for more robust commitments and rapid delivery of assistance from the international community. The President emphasized the importance of all UN member states supporting the UN appeal and providing personnel, equipment, and supplies to stop the epidemic. Both leaders agreed that the international community must redouble their efforts to address the crisis and its devastating impact on the affected countries and their citizens.